p: The highest and lowest frequencies of RSV were in seasonal year 2013 (4002 cases) and 2005 (506 cases), respectively. The majority of RSV cases occurred between January and March, with the most common month being February (see Table A2 for all monthly frequency data). Metapneumovirus rates were highest in seasonal year 2014 (821 cases) and lowest in 2008 (81 cases), with the majority of peak timing usually occurring between January and March, and the most common month being February.
